<h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  " id="details-title">Details</h2>


<div aria-labelledby="details-title">
  
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>This ad hoc statistical release provides detailed breakdowns of the characteristics of disabled and non-disabled people by employment status.</p>

<p>The figures presented are based on data from a number of UK household surveys:</p>

<ul>
  <li>the<a rel="external" href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/employmentandemployeetypes/methodologies/labourforcesurveyuserguidance"> Labour Force Survey and Annual Population Survey</a>, produced by the Office for National Statistics</li>
  <li>the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/family-resources-survey--2">Family Resources Survey</a>, led by the Department for Work and Pensions</li>
  <li>
<a rel="external" href="https://www.understandingsociety.ac.uk/about">Understanding Society</a>, a household longitudinal survey led by a team of scientific experts based at research centres across the UK</li>
</ul>

</div>
</div>

</div>

    </div>

    <div class="app-c-published-dates ">
    Published 1 November 2018
</div>

